This tiny busy shop knows how to do it right. They have a good variety of fried and  grilled seafood served up efficiently. I had the special of the day, fried breaded flounder and french fries and a soda, while my friend chose the healthier grilled fish with salad. My fish and chips was fresh, crispy, and moist without being oily. My friend's dish was also fresh. With the variety of neighboring cuisines available, we were looking for a place to sit. Terrace squeezed in a counter around 2 edges with 6-8 stools that 4 or 5 could sit at comfortably.

Went to Terrace fish and chips today because I had been craving fish for over a week. Ordered the special of the day, fried flounder. Their founder must have been less than a quarter inch thick. It felt like biting into dried pork skins with a thin layer of ham in between. The salad was good, the French fries was sub par. I honestly expected much more from a prime location and for the price I paid for. I am very disappointed in the establishment. Feel a bit cheated out on the fish. Only reason they don't have only one star is because their staff treated is very well. The picture is of my co-worker's founder, ordered the same I had.

Shrimp lovers beware! I ordered extra shrimp and forgive me - asked for additional tartar sauce. The price given to me over the phone was $3.00 less than what I was actually charged. I like their takeout ok but $1.00 per shrimp is excessive and additionally $.50 for the extra tartar sauce  - what the hey???!!! Make sure you're prepared to pay almost $17.00 for lunch. I'm not - they played me over the phone this Friday but no more!

I've tried this place twice. The first time I got the fried fish with salad and seafood rice combo. The second time I got the Cajun tilapia with roasted veggies, salad and seafood rice, this in my opinion was way better than the fried fish I had prior, I think I'll stick to the grilled stuff going forward. The portions were large and at $10-$15 you have enough for two sittings. There's barely seating inside but plenty of seating outside the restaurant.
If you actually like fish and chips, avoid. Fried whiting or flounder, insubstantial verging on slimy.

The prices are fairly high but it's the city, everything is high and this place may be reasonable. However, they only give two pieces of fish in a ten dollar meal. Quick, great food for the price. It's smack in the middle of financial district so it tends to get busy, but worth the wait and they're usually speedy. Seating isn't exactly comfortable especially with customers hustling in and out, but then again it's not really made to be a dine-in place either. Must try the friend or grilled shrimp and seafood rice. Lunch deals are always under $11 or so.

While waiting I realized that the specialty of the place is the burritos, but my fried shrimp and scallops (molluscs similar to very small "scallops") was excellent and easily digestible.
